args: Heeeeey! Nice Saint Starfall outfit, girl!
Since I went to the trouble of making it,\nI figured I might as well wear it right up\nuntil Dragonyule.
Makes sense to me!\nPlus, it looks crazy good on you.
The bells on your ears are particularly\ndelightful.
Oho, what's wrong, Cleo? Your face is\nturnin' redder than Saint Starfall's\nfluffy overcoat!
Ya that stoked to get a compliment from\n{player_name}?
Wh-what are you talking about, Ranzal?!\nCease your idiocy at once!
Ahem! Well, more importantly,\nI've an inquiry for you all.
What kind of food would you all like to\nenjoy at the Dragonyule party?
It's time to start working on a menu,\nbut I fear I'm rather at a loss about\nwhat to prepare.
Oh yeah. Sylvans don't celebrate this\nparticular holiday, yeah?
Correct. As such, I'd like to hear some\nsuggestions from all of you.
A whole roast chicken for everyone!
I wanna tear into that thing until the\njuice runs down my chin!
That's what Dragonyule's all about!\nChicken. ...Oh, and chicken juice.
That's not a bad ideaâ€”despite your\nrather terrifying description.
Perhaps stew, if it's not too much bother?
On Dragonyule Eve, my whole family\nused to gather around the dinner table\nto enjoy piping hot bowls of stew.
Hmm. I may have underestimated the role\nthat food plays in this holiday.
Hell, it only comes around once a year.\nYa gotta grab days like that and shake 'em\ntill every last bit'a fun falls out!
And what would you care to eat,\n{player_name}?
While all this hearty food sounds fantastic,\nall I really want is a slice of cake.
Do humans eat cake during Dragonyule?
I see. Then I shall have to make one.
And what kind of cake would you like?
Hmm... You know, I hadn't thought about\nit in that level of detail yet.
Then let me change the question.
Of all the cakes you've ever eaten,\nwhich was the most delicious?
Oh, that's easy. It's the one my mother\nused to make for me.
She had a special cake she always made\non Dragonyule.
Oh man, that cake was stupid good!
My whole family loved itâ€”even the\npicky ones.
But I've resigned myself to never eating\nit again.
Then I shall prepare it for you.
So long as I know what kind of cake it was,\nI should be able to get reasonably close.
So, would you kindly tell me more about\nthis cake?
It was a traditional Alberian sponge cake\nwith fresh cream on top.
Oh, and she always topped it with\nstrawberries, because they're my favorite.
I think I'm familiar with that kind of cake.
And since it's a fairly simple recipe, \nI should be able to get close to what\nyou remember from your childhood.
I mean, I remember what it tasted like,\nso I can sample the batter and junk to\nmake sure it's the same.
Then you will be my official taste-tester.
I can't wait to try it again.
Rest assured that I will recreate the taste\nas best as I am able.
